# @COMMENT: # @COMMENT: Passage not found in HSNX. Deals with the issue of the loss of a women's hair and according to HJRQV05P077A, as witnessed by WSACD,, in the context of the revelation of Q24:31. HJRQV05P077A appears to be the only Ibn Isḥāq passage that specifically discusses this verse. That it is found in Ibn Ḥajar al-ʿAsqalānī seems odd given the late date of the author. Similar passage also found in WAKMW, WMSAH, WJHZA, and WASKA but do not refer to the same back story or refer to any Qurʾānic verse as a foundation. WSACD and WMSAH gives the witness as ʿĀʾishah not Asmā bint Abī Bakr. 

